The paper deals with algorithms for maintaining a rank-maximal matching in a bipartite graph, which is a problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves game theory concepts such as popular matching, which makes cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) a likely sub-category as well. The use of algorithms and optimization techniques suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on dynamic updates and minimizing changes suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible sub-category.
